We were all very heartened by your
speech last night, Mr. President.

192
00:14:01,208 --> 00:14:03,675
Well, it ain't
gonna be easy.

193
00:14:03,777 --> 00:14:06,444
-<i> It's a difficult time.</i>
- Yes, it is.

194
00:14:06,546 --> 00:14:09,514
But as you suggested,

195
00:14:09,616 --> 00:14:12,550
the greatest tribute
we can pay to President Kennedy

196
00:14:12,652 --> 00:14:14,686
is to enact
his civil rights bill,

197
00:14:14,788 --> 00:14:16,321
especially voting rights.

198
00:14:16,423 --> 00:14:19,657
Yeah, well, you're preaching
to the choir there, Reverend.

199
00:14:19,759 --> 00:14:23,194
Voting rights is the meat
of the coconut,

200
00:14:23,296 --> 00:14:26,197
and we're gonna pass
that bill as is

201
00:14:26,299 --> 00:14:27,532
