1150
01:02:22,740 --> 01:02:24,873
It's the passing
of an era.

1151
01:02:24,975 --> 01:02:26,408
Well, yes, it is.

1152
01:02:26,510 --> 01:02:30,345
It's the passing of a time
of etiquette, courtesy.

1153
01:02:30,447 --> 01:02:33,115
It's the passing
of a time of principles,

1154
01:02:33,217 --> 01:02:34,616
like party unity.

1155
01:02:36,553 --> 01:02:39,921
You know what the old
soldier said on parade?

1156
01:02:40,023 --> 01:02:43,458
"Hey, look, everybody's
out of step but me."

1157
01:02:43,560 --> 01:02:44,960
Maybe.

1158
01:02:45,062 --> 01:02:49,097
I am old, that's true,
and God knows I'm tired.

1159
01:02:49,199 --> 01:02:51,299
But the fellas
coming up behind me

1160
01:02:51,401 --> 01:02:54,436
are utterly without
principle of any kind

1161
01:02:54,538 --> 01:02:57,205
and you'll see how you like
dealing with them.

1162
01:02:58,575 --> 01:03:01,009
You're gonna miss me
when I'm gone.

1163
01:03:01,111 --> 01:03:04,212
I still need you, Dick.

1164
01:03:05,382 --> 01:03:08,717
I'm still here,
Mr. President.

1165
01:03:08,819 --> 01:03:11,419
But the rest of Dixie?

1166
01:03:14,224 --> 01:03:17,425
I hope you haven't just killed
your election chances.

1167
01:03:25,035 --> 01:03:26,735
Congratulations,
Mr. President,

1168
01:03:26,837 --> 01:03:29,404
on your glorious
achievement.

1169
01:03:30,374 --> 01:03:33,508
The Democratic Party
just lost the South

1170
01:03:33,610 --> 01:03:35,777
for the rest
of my lifetime

1171
01:03:35,879 --> 01:03:38,213
