<i>in the final seconds</i> <i>with
a handful</i> <i>of fake votes,</i>

1194
01:04:56,693 --> 01:04:58,927
<i>and I will carry</i>
<i>the pain of that with me</i>

1195
01:04:59,029 --> 01:05:01,129
<i>to my dying day.</i>

1196
01:05:01,231 --> 01:05:02,797
<i>But I'll tell you what.</i>

1197
01:05:02,900 --> 01:05:07,068
<i>Nobody will ever</i>
<i>do me that way again.</i>

1198
01:05:07,170 --> 01:05:11,239
- Goldwater:...that every fiber of my being...
-<i> It'll be some other way.</i>

1199
01:05:11,341 --> 01:05:14,910
Goldwater: <i>...that nothing shall
be</i> <i>lacking from the struggle...</i>

1200
01:05:58,288 --> 01:05:59,988
Out of the car, boys.

1201
01:06:00,090 --> 01:06:02,057
What's the problem,
Deputy Price?

1202
01:06:02,159 --> 01:06:03,625
I thought we were good.

1203
01:06:03,727 --> 01:06:07,162
Out of the car,
Jew boy.

1204
01:06:32,222 --> 01:06:34,923
Man: <i>What you</i>
<i>looking at, nigger?</i>

1205
01:06:36,460 --> 01:06:38,626
We've got a situation
in Mississippi.

1206
01:06:38,729 --> 01:06:41,563
- Johnson:<i> Yeah?</i>
- Three young men have gone missing.

1207
01:06:41,665 --> 01:06:44,132
Michael Schwerner,
age 25,

1208
01:06:44,234 --> 01:06:45,967
Andrew Goodman,
age 21,

1209
01:06:46,069 --> 01:06:48,036
and James Chaney, 21.

1210
01:06:48,138 --> 01:06:51,373
They were all working the Freedom
Summer project in Meridian.

1211
01:06:51,475 --> 01:06:53,475
<i>Chaney's a local Negro,</i>

1212
01:06:53,577 --> 01:06:57,779
<i>but Schwerner and Goodman</i> <i>were
both out-of-state</i> <i>volunteers,</i>

1213
01:06:57,881 --> 01:06:59,447
<i>both white.</i>

1214
01:06:59,549 --> 01:07:02,917
Well, the shit
will hit the fan now.

1215
01:07:04,721 --> 01:07:06,454
Get me the governor
of Mississippi.

1216
01:07:06,556 --> 01:07:08,523
They were investigating
the burning

1217
01:07:08,625 --> 01:07:10,458
of a Negro church
in Neshoba County.

1218
01:07:10,560 --> 01:07:13,395
They've been missing
for 15 hours now.

1219
01:07:14,598 --> 01:07:17,098
Missing in Mississippi?

1220
01:07:17,200 --> 01:07:20,068
Son of a bitch.

1221
01:07:21,338 --> 01:07:24,005
Yeah. All right,
put him through.

1222
01:07:24,107 --> 01:07:27,809
- - Governor, I'm calling
about those three boys.

1223
01:07:27,911 --> 01:07:30,345
You mean those three
professional agitators.

1224
01:07:30,447 --> 01:07:32,680
<i>Chaney, Schwerner,</i>
<i>and Goodman.</i>

1225
01:07:32,783 --> 01:07:36,418
Yeah, that come into our state
creating all kinds of problems.

1226
01:07:36,520 --> 01:07:39,721
Apparently,
a Deputy Price

1227
01:07:39,823 --> 01:07:41,756
arrested them
yesterday afternoon.

1228
01:07:41,858 --> 01:07:44,959
For driving 35 miles
over the speed limit.

1229
01:07:45,062 --> 01:07:46,561
- Really?
-<i> Yes, sir.</i>

1230
01:07:46,663 --> 01:07:49,798
So they held them
for a couple hours.

1231
01:07:49,900 --> 01:07:52,267
<i>Oh, see, now that's</i>
<i>where it gets confusing</i>

1232
01:07:52,369 --> 01:07:56,237
'cause when their friends
called the jail down there,

1233
01:07:56,339 --> 01:08:00,075
the deputy said
he had never heard of them.

1234
01:08:00,177 --> 01:08:03,244
Well, I don't know
anything about that.

1235
01:08:03,346 --> 01:08:06,014
Uh, Price said

1236
01:08:06,116 --> 01:08:09,684
he released them
at 10:00 that night.

1237
01:08:09,786 --> 01:08:11,619
And nobody's
heard of them since.

1238
01:08:11,721 --> 01:08:16,191
This is clearly
a publicity stunt.

1239
01:08:16,293 --> 01:08:19,494
Well, those boys
are off hiding somewhere

1240
01:08:19,596 --> 01:08:21,596
<i>probably having themselves</i>
<i>a good laugh,</i>

1241
01:08:21,698 --> 01:08:23,364
<i>and they're gonna</i>
<i>come back in,</i>

1242
01:08:23,467 --> 01:08:25,633
<i>they're gonna claim they were</i>
<i>abused or something.</i>

1243
01:08:25,735 --> 01:08:27,168
Well, now, I'd hate
to have to send

1244
01:08:27,270 --> 01:08:29,904
a whole bunch of federal
marshals into your state.

1245
01:08:30,006 --> 01:08:33,541
Uh, well, no,
you don't wanna do that.

1246
01:08:33,643 --> 01:08:34,943
<i>Of course I don't.</i>

1247
01:08:35,045 --> 01:08:36,478
You don't want
the publicity

1248
01:08:36,580 --> 01:08:38,513
and I sure as hell
don't wanna stir up a mess

1249
01:08:38,615 --> 01:08:40,682
just eight weeks before
the Democratic Convention.

1250
01:08:40,784 --> 01:08:43,751
<i>But there's</i> <i>a lot of
pressure</i> <i>to do something.</i>

1251
01:08:43,854 --> 01:08:45,720
<i>Now, if you'd rather,</i>

1252
01:08:45,822 --> 01:08:49,891
<i>I guess I can</i> <i>get a few FBI
agents</i> <i>to look into the thing.</i>

1253
01:08:49,993 --> 01:08:51,559
FBI?

1254
01:08:51,661 --> 01:08:53,328
Well,
it's a damn sight better

1255
01:08:53,430 --> 01:08:55,964
than the federal marshals
and the US Army, isn't it?

1256
01:08:56,066 --> 01:09:00,135
Well, yes,
I guess it would.

1257
01:09:00,237 --> 01:09:01,369
Yeah, you know,
I think

1258
01:09:01,471 --> 01:09:03,938
you got the right idea
there, Governor.

1259
01:09:04,040 --> 01:09:07,509
Let this be Hoover's problem, not ours.

1260
01:09:07,611 --> 01:09:09,310
Hopefully, you're right
about the whole thing

1261
01:09:09,412 --> 01:09:12,647
and these boys will turn up
quick and we can all just relax.

1262
01:09:12,749 --> 01:09:14,883
Christ's sakes,
we got an election to win.

1263
01:09:14,985 --> 01:09:16,484
Hoover will just
drag his feet.

1264
01:09:16,586 --> 01:09:18,887
No, not if I light
a fire under his ass.

1265
01:09:25,028 --> 01:09:27,495
- Mr. President.
-<i> Edgar,</i>

1266
01:09:27,597 --> 01:09:29,731
the governor
of Mississippi

1267
01:09:29,833 --> 01:09:33,168
wants the FBI to look
into these missing kids.

1268
01:09:33,270 --> 01:09:36,070
Well, I'd be happy to,
Mr. President,

1269
01:09:36,173 --> 01:09:37,739
but there's
a jurisdictional problem.

1270
01:09:37,841 --> 01:09:40,308
Well, I'm not gonna tell you
how to run your shop,

1271
01:09:40,410 --> 01:09:44,045
but, uh, the governor
asked specifically

1272
01:09:44,147 --> 01:09:46,214
for the FBI
to investigate.

1273
01:09:46,316 --> 01:09:50,318
I tried to put him off,
but, uh, well, I suppose

1274
01:09:50,420 --> 01:09:53,454
I can get
some third party involved.

1275
01:09:53,557 --> 01:09:55,223
I know Senator
Jim Eastland

1276
01:09:55,325 --> 01:09:56,958
wants Allen Dulles
investigating.

1277
01:09:57,060 --> 01:09:59,694
CIA? Oh, no,
Mr. President,

1278
01:09:59,796 --> 01:10:02,030
I don't think Dulles
is a good idea.

1279
01:10:02,132 --> 01:10:04,999
This is very clearly
an FBI matter.

1280
01:10:05,101 --> 01:10:07,335
<i>Well, if you're sure.</i>

1281
01:10:07,437 --> 01:10:10,071
<i>I mean, the last thing</i>
<i>I would want</i>

1282
01:10:10,173 --> 01:10:13,775
<i>is Dulles down there</i> <i>acting like
he was running</i> <i>the FBI as well.</i>

1283
01:10:13,877 --> 01:10:17,612
I'll tell you what, let's
say Eastland is my problem.

1284
01:10:17,714 --> 01:10:18,880
I'll just deal with him.

1285
01:10:18,982 --> 01:10:21,082
You get your agents down there
to Neshoba County

1286
01:10:21,184 --> 01:10:23,418
and you just wrap this
thing up quick, you hear?

1287
01:10:23,520 --> 01:10:25,920
When did you talk
to Eastland

1288
01:10:26,022 --> 01:10:27,989
about Dulles
going down there?

1289
01:10:28,091 --> 01:10:30,592
Oh, I made that part up.

1290
01:10:30,694 --> 01:10:34,963
The problem here is there's
three sovereignties involved.

1291
01:10:35,065 --> 01:10:37,031
There's the United States,

1292
01:10:37,133 --> 01:10:40,034
there's the state
of Mississippi,

1293
01:10:40,136 --> 01:10:43,304
and then there's
J. Edgar Hoover.

1294
01:10:50,947 --> 01:10:54,082
Reporter: <i>The burned-out station
wagon</i> <i>was discovered in the woods</i>

1295
01:10:54,184 --> 01:10:56,284
<i>20 miles from Philadelphia,</i>
<i>Mississippi,</i>

1296
01:10:56,386 --> 01:10:59,087
<i>a small town</i> <i>in which
Schwerner,</i> <i>Goodman, and Chaney</i>

1297
01:10:59,189 --> 01:11:01,589
<i>had been arrested for speeding</i>
<i>during the day.</i>

1298
01:11:01,691 --> 01:11:04,225
<i>They were released</i> <i>late at
night by</i> <i>a deputy sheriff</i>

1299
01:11:04,327 --> 01:11:07,795
<i>and were last seen driving away</i>
<i>in the blue station wagon.</i>

1300
01:11:07,897 --> 01:11:11,132
- We have to assume those young
men are dead. - Wilkins: Mm-hmm.

1301
01:11:11,234 --> 01:11:13,101
There were no bodies
in the car they found.

1302
01:11:13,203 --> 01:11:16,671
Oh, well, then they're probably
on vacation, huh, Mr. Wilkins?

1303
01:11:16,773 --> 01:11:19,007
I mean, I always
set my car on fire

1304
01:11:19,109 --> 01:11:20,675
before taking
a weekend off.

1305
01:11:20,777 --> 01:11:23,411
How many voters
have you actually registered?

1306
01:11:27,117 --> 01:11:29,550
- 1,200, give or take.
- Hmm.

1307
01:11:29,653 --> 01:11:32,553
500 beaten and arrested,
35 churches burned,

1308
01:11:32,656 --> 01:11:34,555
30 Negro homes
and businesses

1309
01:11:34,658 --> 01:11:38,259
dynamited
for 1,200 votes.

1310
01:11:38,361 --> 01:11:40,261
It's not just
about the votes.

1311
01:11:40,363 --> 01:11:43,865
For the first time, black people
are building a new political party.

1312
01:11:43,967 --> 01:11:46,734
- The Mississippi Freedom Democratic Party, I heard.
- Carmichael:<i> Hold on.</i>

1313
01:11:46,836 --> 01:11:49,203
We tried to play
by the rules

1314
01:11:49,306 --> 01:11:52,774
of the regular Democrat
Party, but they kept us out.

1315
01:11:52,876 --> 01:11:57,478
Fine. So we built our own Democrat
Party, but with a difference.

1316
01:11:57,580 --> 01:12:00,348
Open to everybody,
white or Negro.

1317
01:12:00,450 --> 01:12:03,651
Well, don't you think that America ought
to have at least one political party

1318
01:12:03,753 --> 01:12:05,453
- that isn't racist?
- It's a waste of time.

1319
01:12:05,555 --> 01:12:08,323
We send our delegates
to the convention

1320
01:12:08,425 --> 01:12:09,924
where they challenge
the legality

1321
01:12:10,026 --> 01:12:12,927
of the segregated Mississippi
delegation on national TV

1322
01:12:13,029 --> 01:12:17,799
- and dare L.B.J.
- not to seat us.

1323
01:12:18,835 --> 01:12:21,202
Children playing
with dynamite.

1324
01:12:21,304 --> 01:12:24,105
Are you so desperate
for their approval

1325
01:12:24,207 --> 01:12:27,442
that you would sanction
this mass suicide?

1326
01:12:27,544 --> 01:12:30,211
Those young men
went down to Mississippi

1327
01:12:30,313 --> 01:12:33,815
and died doing the work the
government hasn't been willing to do

1328
01:12:33,917 --> 01:12:36,384
for a hundred years.

1329
01:12:36,486 --> 01:12:38,753
We've got
to take a stand.

1330
01:12:43,893 --> 01:12:46,294
I grieve
for those young men.

1331
01:12:47,163 --> 01:12:48,863
Don't use
their funeral pyre

1332
01:12:48,965 --> 01:12:51,499
to burn what's left
of the movement.

1333
01:12:59,075 --> 01:13:01,209
How can I help, Bob?

1334
01:13:01,311 --> 01:13:03,678
- Come to Mississippi.
- Don't be ridiculous.

1335
01:13:03,780 --> 01:13:06,647
Show the people that you are
behind the Mississippi Freedom-

1336
01:13:06,750 --> 01:13:09,350
You might as well
paint a target on his back

1337
01:13:09,452 --> 01:13:10,718
and declare open season.

1338
01:13:10,820 --> 01:13:13,287
Martin, you have not
been to Mississippi

1339
01:13:13,390 --> 01:13:15,089
- in over a year.
- Abernathy:<i> He's been busy.</i>

1340
01:13:15,191 --> 01:13:17,725
Death threats,
jail, shot at.

1341
01:13:17,827 --> 01:13:22,230
- You don't own a monopoly over
suffering- - And I never said that I did.

1342
01:13:22,332 --> 01:13:24,632
Let somebody else
carry this one, Martin.

1343
01:13:26,336 --> 01:13:28,102
<i>Please.</i>

1344
01:13:35,278 --> 01:13:38,112
Of course I'll come.

1345
01:13:38,214 --> 01:13:42,250
Jenkins: <i>FBI was acting on a tip
about</i> <i>a farm in rural Mississippi</i>

1346
01:13:42,352 --> 01:13:45,386
<i>and they just found</i> <i>two bodies
buried there</i> <i>in an earthen dam.</i>

1347
01:13:45,488 --> 01:13:48,122
Jesus.
Are they sure it's them?

1348
01:13:48,224 --> 01:13:50,191
Schwerner's draft card
in his back pocket.

1349
01:13:50,293 --> 01:13:52,326
Goodman's body
right below his.

1350
01:13:52,429 --> 01:13:55,196
It appears they had both
been shot once in the chest.

1351
01:13:55,298 --> 01:13:57,098
And they're
still digging for Chaney.

1352
01:13:57,200 --> 01:13:59,500
God damn.

1353
01:13:59,602 --> 01:14:01,569
Bless those boys.

1354
01:14:02,739 --> 01:14:05,606
The minute McNamara
gets here, you send him in.

1355
01:14:07,510 --> 01:14:11,212
Gentlemen, we need to pick up
this conversation some other time.

1356
01:14:11,314 --> 01:14:13,347
I'm sorry.

1357
01:14:13,450 --> 01:14:17,819
It's obvious that
this Deputy Price

1358
01:14:17,921 --> 01:14:19,020
was involved in that.

1359
01:14:19,122 --> 01:14:20,788
Probably
the sheriff, too.

1360
01:14:20,890 --> 01:14:22,256
Oh, Lord.

1361
01:14:22,358 --> 01:14:25,626
- Well, this whole mess
is in my lap now.

1362
01:14:25,728 --> 01:14:28,196
If I don't charge
these bastards,

1363
01:14:28,298 --> 01:14:31,199
then King yells and I'm letting
them get away with murder.

1364
01:14:31,301 --> 01:14:34,402
But if I do charge them,
then all the Southerners scream

1365
01:14:34,504 --> 01:14:36,704
about how I'm taking orders
from the Negroes,

1366
01:14:36,806 --> 01:14:40,274
and all this two weeks before the
start of the goddamn convention.

1367
01:14:40,376 --> 01:14:42,510
Mr. President, I'm sorry
to have to tell you,

1368
01:14:42,612 --> 01:14:44,111
but the word is
Governor Wallace

1369
01:14:44,214 --> 01:14:45,580
has offered himself
to Goldwater

1370
01:14:45,682 --> 01:14:49,050
as the Republican vice
presidential candidate.

1371
01:14:49,152 --> 01:14:50,952
That little weasel

1372
01:14:51,054 --> 01:14:53,221
would sell his mother
to get a leg up.

1373
01:14:53,323 --> 01:14:56,991
And Strom Thurmond
is formally switching parties.

1374
01:14:57,093 --> 01:14:58,860
That motherfucker!

1375
01:14:58,962 --> 01:15:00,862
<i>Is anybody</i>
<i>gonna follow him?</i>

1376
01:15:00,964 --> 01:15:03,364
- Well, I don't know.
- Well, find out.

1377
01:15:03,466 --> 01:15:06,300
- You bet I will.
- God damn it.

1378
01:15:13,443 --> 01:15:15,776
You see her on TV?

1379
01:15:15,879 --> 01:15:18,579
- Who?
- Oh, the-

1380
01:15:18,681 --> 01:15:21,516
the dead kid's wife,
Schwerner.

1381
01:15:21,618 --> 01:15:23,985
Uh, Rita, Rita.

1382
01:15:24,087 --> 01:15:27,154
Wife.
Widow, I mean.

1383
01:15:27,257 --> 01:15:28,456
Christ.

1384
01:15:28,558 --> 01:15:30,291
Terrible.

1385
01:15:30,393 --> 01:15:33,427
- - Mr. President,
we have word.

1386
01:15:34,597 --> 01:15:37,431
No, no. Come on.

1387
01:15:38,601 --> 01:15:40,568
Yeah. Sit there.

1388
01:15:41,704 --> 01:15:43,571
All right, Robert.

1389
01:15:43,673 --> 01:15:46,340
Captain Herrick
of the USS Maddox

1390
01:15:46,442 --> 01:15:48,976
reports a potential
sighting last night

1391
01:15:49,078 --> 01:15:53,748
of two possibly hostile unidentified
vessels in the Gulf of Tonkin

1392
01:15:53,850 --> 01:15:56,951
and some somewhat
contradictory sonar evidence

1393
01:15:57,053 --> 01:15:58,853
of actual
torpedo attack.

1394
01:16:00,623 --> 01:16:02,957
Wh- a potential sighting?

1395
01:16:03,059 --> 01:16:05,326
What the hell's
a potential sighting?

1396
01:16:05,428 --> 01:16:08,663
A visual sighting not
confirmed by mechanical means.

1397
01:16:10,033 --> 01:16:12,767
And this torpedo attack,
this actually happened?

1398
01:16:12,869 --> 01:16:15,970
Still awaiting
confirmation.

1399
01:16:16,072 --> 01:16:19,273
Well, were any
of our ships hit?

1400
01:16:19,375 --> 01:16:20,675
No, sir.

1401
01:16:20,777 --> 01:16:24,211
-<i> Were there any explosions?</i>
- No, sir.

1402
01:16:24,314 --> 01:16:27,448
Then how the hell do we know
we were attacked?

1403
01:16:27,550 --> 01:16:29,717
We don't, for sure.

1404
01:16:29,819 --> 01:16:33,254
We have contradictory
sonar readings.

1405
01:16:33,356 --> 01:16:35,089
For God's sakes, Robert.

1406
01:16:35,191 --> 01:16:37,224
Give me something
I could work with here.

1407
01:16:37,327 --> 01:16:42,029
Officially, this is
a very delicate subject.

1408
01:16:42,832 --> 01:16:45,299
Oh, Humphrey can know.

1409
01:16:46,502 --> 01:16:48,269
Mr. President,

1410
01:16:48,371 --> 01:16:50,538
the limited air strikes
you ordered preselected

1411
01:16:50,640 --> 01:16:53,341
- in case of another attack are good to go.
- Air strikes?

1412
01:16:53,443 --> 01:16:56,143
- Shall we order them in?
- Surely, this is a situation

1413
01:16:56,245 --> 01:16:58,512
about which we ought to be
more confident before we act.

1414
01:16:58,615 --> 01:17:02,283
There's no sense in pretending last
night's event didn't happen, not anymore.

1415
01:17:02,385 --> 01:17:05,419
- What do you mean?
- There's been a leak somewhere.

1416
01:17:05,521 --> 01:17:08,823
- Who? Who leaked it?
- We're tracking it down.

1417
01:17:08,925 --> 01:17:10,658
I want his fucking head
in a basket!

1418
01:17:10,760 --> 01:17:14,762
The point is the press
has got to it somehow.

1419
01:17:14,864 --> 01:17:16,497
God damn it!

1420
01:17:16,599 --> 01:17:20,034
