01:43:47,555 --> 01:43:50,556
Announcer: <i>Will the delegates</i>
<i>please be seated?</i>

1894
01:43:50,658 --> 01:43:54,327
<i>A workable compromise</i>
<i>regarding at large delegates</i>

1895
01:43:54,429 --> 01:43:56,229
-<i> from Mississippi</i> <i>has been reached.</i>
- All right.

1896
01:43:56,331 --> 01:43:58,431
All right, that's it.
We're leaving. Come on.

1897
01:43:58,533 --> 01:44:00,833
<i>And we urge the delegates here</i>
<i>to approve the recommendations</i>

1898
01:44:00,935 --> 01:44:04,003
-<i> of the credentials committee.</i>
- Jim, what the hell's going on?

1899
01:44:04,105 --> 01:44:06,072
L.B.J. screwed us over.

1900
01:44:06,174 --> 01:44:08,341
He's seating the niggers.

1901
01:44:10,612 --> 01:44:12,511
You boys just stay here.
I'll figure this out.

1902
01:44:12,614 --> 01:44:15,481
Reporter: <i>The credentials committee</i>
<i>settled on a compromise</i>

1903
01:44:15,583 --> 01:44:17,817
<i>of two voting delegates</i>
<i>for the MFDP,</i>

1904
01:44:17,919 --> 01:44:22,388
<i>but Mississippi and Alabama</i>
<i>rejected the deal</i> <i>and walked out.</i>

1905
01:44:22,490 --> 01:44:24,056
<i>If Georgia</i>
<i>walks out next,</i>

1906
01:44:24,158 --> 01:44:28,094
-<i> the rest of the South</i> <i>will follow.</i>
- Mr. President?

1907
01:44:28,196 --> 01:44:31,030
<i>It's Governor Sanders</i>
<i>of Georgia on the phone.</i>

1908
01:44:31,132 --> 01:44:33,432
What, it's Georgia?

1909
01:44:33,534 --> 01:44:34,867
What the hell
does Carl want?

1910
01:44:34,969 --> 01:44:37,203
Alabama and Mississippi
are walking out

1911
01:44:37,305 --> 01:44:39,071
and Sanders says
he might follow.

1912
01:44:39,173 --> 01:44:40,873
<i>God damn it!</i>

1913
01:44:42,110 --> 01:44:43,743
Carl, what the hell
is going on?

1914
01:44:43,845 --> 01:44:47,513
Mr. President, you can't give
these people two seats.

1915
01:44:47,615 --> 01:44:50,583
It's gonna look like the Negroes
are taking over the whole convention.

1916
01:44:50,685 --> 01:44:52,251
Oh, for Christ's sakes,

1917
01:44:52,353 --> 01:44:55,054
it's one Negro
and one white minister.

1918
01:44:55,156 --> 01:44:57,056
Now, it's the principle
of the thing.

1919
01:44:57,158 --> 01:44:59,859
Me and my delegates are
about inches from walking out.

1920
01:44:59,961 --> 01:45:01,627
In fact, the whole
South's about to bolt.

1921
01:45:01,729 --> 01:45:03,629
All right,
now let's you and me

1922
01:45:03,731 --> 01:45:05,197
understand something here.

1923
01:45:05,300 --> 01:45:08,834
Those people are Democrats
just like you and me,

1924
01:45:08,936 --> 01:45:11,570
but those good old boys from
Mississippi, they locked them out.

1925
01:45:11,673 --> 01:45:13,239
Well, now,
they got locked out

1926
01:45:13,341 --> 01:45:14,573
because they're
not registered to vote.

1927
01:45:14,676 --> 01:45:16,976
Because they wouldn't
let them register!

1928
01:45:17,078 --> 01:45:20,613
They beat them and shot them
and lynched them.

1929
01:45:20,715 --> 01:45:22,882
Well, now, you're tarring a lot
of people here, Mr. President.

1930
01:45:22,984 --> 01:45:25,818
No, Carl, Carl, you and I
just can't survive

1931
01:45:25,920 --> 01:45:29,889
our modern political life with
these goddamn fellas down there

1932
01:45:29,991 --> 01:45:34,493
doing things the old way and eating
them Negroes for breakfast every morning.

1933
01:45:34,595 --> 01:45:35,661
They got to quit that!

1934
01:45:35,763 --> 01:45:38,597
Mr. President,
you need to remove

1935
01:45:38,700 --> 01:45:40,633
these so-called
delegates at large.

1936
01:45:40,735 --> 01:45:43,202
No, you listen to me!

1937
01:45:43,304 --> 01:45:45,705
You need to make up your mind
once and for all

1938
01:45:45,807 --> 01:45:48,007
what- what kind
of Christian you are.

1939
01:45:48,109 --> 01:45:50,376
Are you
a once-a-week fella

1940
01:45:50,478 --> 01:45:53,079
or do you hold the Word
in your heart?

1941
01:45:53,181 --> 01:45:56,382
<i>And what kind</i>
<i>of politician are you?</i>

1942
01:45:56,484 --> 01:45:58,851
<i>You just</i>
<i>out for yourself</i>

1943
01:45:58,953 --> 01:46:02,188
<i>or you wanna make</i> <i>a better life
for all</i> <i>the people of Georgia?</i>

1944
01:46:02,290 --> 01:46:04,890
- Well, of course I- -<i> And what
kind</i> <i>of man are you?</i>

1945
01:46:04,992 --> 01:46:09,295
You got the balls to do
what you know is right

1946
01:46:09,397 --> 01:46:12,598
<i>or do you</i>
<i>just slink away?</i>

1947
01:46:12,700 --> 01:46:15,801
Now, what you don't get to do
is threaten me.

1948
01:46:15,903 --> 01:46:17,703
So if you're gonna walk out
of the convention,

1949
01:46:17,805 --> 01:46:19,338
then you just do it
right now!

1950
01:46:19,440 --> 01:46:21,507
<i>But if not,</i>

1951
01:46:21,609 --> 01:46:24,744
then I expect to see
your bright and shiny faces

1952
01:46:24,846 --> 01:46:28,314
wearing your big "All the way
with L.B.J." hats tonight

1953
01:46:28,416 --> 01:46:30,282
when I take the stage.

1954
01:46:36,924 --> 01:46:39,125
Bird, go away
and leave me be.

1955
01:46:39,227 --> 01:46:41,427
I can't do that,
Lyndon.

1956
01:46:41,529 --> 01:46:43,095
I won't.

1957
01:46:44,165 --> 01:46:46,499
You're just like
the rest of them.

1958
01:46:46,601 --> 01:46:48,667
You're all against me.

1959
01:46:48,770 --> 01:46:51,170
That is so not true.

1960
01:46:51,272 --> 01:46:54,140
- Oh, yeah?
- Look at me.

1961
01:46:55,009 --> 01:46:57,109
Look at me, Lyndon.

1962
01:47:00,314 --> 01:47:02,581
You are as brave a man

1963
01:47:02,683 --> 01:47:07,219
as FDR and Truman
and Lincoln.

1964
01:47:07,321 --> 01:47:09,588
And there are
many, many people

1965
01:47:09,690 --> 01:47:12,158
up there
at that convention

1966
01:47:12,260 --> 01:47:14,160
and in this party

1967
01:47:14,262 --> 01:47:17,930
and in this nation
who love you.

1968
01:47:18,032 --> 01:47:22,001
- And they are counting on you.
- I'm gonna resign.

1969
01:47:22,103 --> 01:47:24,136
- Let somebody else deal with this.
- You're not going to resign.

1970
01:47:24,238 --> 01:47:25,738
- Yes, I am!
- No, you are not!

1971
01:47:25,840 --> 01:47:28,474
- When your
great-grandmother... - Oh!

1972
01:47:28,576 --> 01:47:30,242
...was hiding
in the floorboards

1973
01:47:30,344 --> 01:47:33,379
while the Comanches
were raiding her house,

1974
01:47:33,481 --> 01:47:35,314
did she flinch?

1975
01:47:35,416 --> 01:47:39,118
To step down now would
be wrong for your country.

1976
01:47:39,220 --> 01:47:42,788
Your friends would be
frozen with embarrassment

1977
01:47:42,890 --> 01:47:44,924
and your enemies
would jeer.

1978
01:47:46,060 --> 01:47:48,494
Those bastards would love
to see me down.

1979
01:47:48,596 --> 01:47:50,529
And are you gonna
give them that pleasure?

1980
01:47:50,631 --> 01:47:52,865
I don't think so.

1981
01:47:52,967 --> 01:47:55,201
That is not
the man I married.

1982
01:47:55,303 --> 01:47:57,470
Sir, Governor Sanders
was just on TV

1983
01:47:57,572 --> 01:48:00,439
and the Georgia delegation's
not gonna walk out after all.

1984
01:48:01,709 --> 01:48:04,977
- What, Sanders backed down?
-<i> Yes, sir, he did.</i>

1985
01:48:05,079 --> 01:48:09,548
- So the South held?
- Yes, sir.

1986
01:48:09,650 --> 01:48:13,085
- - Announcer:<i> The Honorable</i>
<i>Lyndon B. Johnson</i>

1987
01:48:13,187 --> 01:48:15,020
<i>is nominated</i>
<i>by acclamation</i>

1988
01:48:15,122 --> 01:48:17,122
<i>as our candidate</i>
<i>to the office</i>

1989
01:48:17,225 --> 01:48:19,758
<i>of President</i>
<i>of the United States</i>

1990
01:48:19,861 --> 01:48:22,962
<i>and the Honorable</i>
<i>Hubert Horatio Humphrey</i>

1991
01:48:23,064 --> 01:48:25,531
<i>is our candidate</i>
<i>for Vice President!</i>

1992
01:48:25,633 --> 01:48:27,867
The dust has settled
here in Atlantic City

1993
01:48:27,969 --> 01:48:30,402
<i>and President Johnson's</i>
<i>Democratic Party</i>

1994
01:48:30,505 --> 01:48:32,705
<i>is one big,</i>
<i>happy family.</i>

1995
01:48:32,807 --> 01:48:34,573
<i>Hello there!</i>

1996
01:48:36,377 --> 01:48:37,810
<i>- Hubert.</i>
<i>- Mr. President.</i>

1997
01:48:37,912 --> 01:48:39,478
<i>You look a little down</i>
<i>in the mouth</i>

1998
01:48:39,580 --> 01:48:41,647
<i>for being the next</i>
<i>vice president.</i>

1999
01:48:41,749 --> 01:48:44,950
<i>It just feels different</i>
<i>than I thought it would.</i>

2000
01:48:45,052 --> 01:48:47,119
<i>Oh, that.</i>
<i>Well...</i>

2001
01:48:47,221 --> 01:48:49,421
<i>you get over that</i>
<i>pretty quick.</i>

2002
01:48:49,524 --> 01:48:54,627
Announcer: <i>The American people have</i>
<i>no greater advocate and friend</i>

2003
01:48:54,729 --> 01:48:57,162
<i>than the man</i>
<i>the Democratic Party</i>

2004
01:48:57,265 --> 01:49:00,399
<i>is proud to claim</i>
<i>as our leader.</i>

2005
01:49:00,501 --> 01:49:02,668
<i>Now the man of the hour,</i>

2006
01:49:02,770 --> 01:49:05,037
<i> Lyndon Baines Johnson!</i>

2007
01:49:05,139 --> 01:49:08,073
<i>♪ The skies above</i>
<i>are clear again ♪</i>

2008
01:49:08,175 --> 01:49:12,044
<i>♪ Let us sing a song</i>
<i>of cheer again ♪</i>

2009
01:49:12,146 --> 01:49:16,982
<i>♪ Happy days</i>
<i>are here again. ♪</i>

2010
01:49:17,084 --> 01:49:18,951
We're down five points
in Georgia,

2011
01:49:19,053 --> 01:49:21,120
six points
in South Carolina,

2012
01:49:21,222 --> 01:49:23,355
eight points
in Louisiana.

2013
01:49:23,457 --> 01:49:26,425
Hell, Goldwater
is beating my ass

2014
01:49:26,527 --> 01:49:28,928
by 60% in Mississippi.

2015
01:49:29,030 --> 01:49:30,629
Now, he's getting on top!

2016
01:49:30,731 --> 01:49:33,265
Son of a bitch
is turning it around!

2017
01:49:33,367 --> 01:49:35,301
Where the hell
are the ideas?

2018
01:49:35,403 --> 01:49:36,969
Where the hell's
the solutions?

2019
01:49:37,071 --> 01:49:39,605
Walter, I want you to change
my travel schedule.

2020
01:49:39,707 --> 01:49:42,675
Give me more time in the
South, especially Louisiana.

2021
01:49:42,777 --> 01:49:45,311
- And put more money into our TV campaign down there.
- Yes, sir.

2022
01:49:45,413 --> 01:49:48,747
And as for the rest of you, what the
hell are you still standing here for?

2023
01:49:48,849 --> 01:49:50,783
Get out there
and do something!

2024
01:49:50,885 --> 01:49:51,850
Come on.

2025
01:49:51,953 --> 01:49:54,520
Not you, Humphrey.
Stay here.

2026
01:49:54,622 --> 01:49:59,291
You read this bullshit "Wall Street
Journal" exposé about my corruption?

2027
01:49:59,393 --> 01:50:01,694
Definitely planted
by Goldwater.

2028
01:50:01,796 --> 01:50:03,429
Damn right it was.

2029
01:50:03,531 --> 01:50:06,031
Take a look at this.

2030
01:50:06,133 --> 01:50:09,735
- Huh?
- That's disgusting.

2031
01:50:09,837 --> 01:50:12,605
Goldwater wants
to get down into the mud,

2032
01:50:12,707 --> 01:50:14,740
by God,
I could do that.

2033
01:50:14,842 --> 01:50:17,276
Listen here, I want you
to pull together

2034
01:50:17,378 --> 01:50:19,411
a special group
separate from the campaign

2035
01:50:19,513 --> 01:50:21,347
and hit him back
with everything we got!

2036
01:50:21,449 --> 01:50:24,283
Mr. President, I don't think
sinking to their level is-

2037
01:50:24,385 --> 01:50:26,685
Oh, for God's sake,
just do it.

2038
01:50:26,787 --> 01:50:31,624
Mr. President, you are ahead in
the polls in most of the country.

2039
01:50:31,726 --> 01:50:34,460
Yeah, and so was
Nixon in '60.

2040
01:50:34,562 --> 01:50:36,929
And some people thought
he would've beat Jack

2041
01:50:37,031 --> 01:50:38,964
except for a whole bunch
of dead people

2042
01:50:39,066 --> 01:50:41,100
voting in Chicago
at the last minute.

2043
01:50:41,202 --> 01:50:44,570
It ain't over
until it's over.

2044
01:50:46,140 --> 01:50:49,541
...eight, nine-

2045
01:50:51,078 --> 01:50:54,079
- nine...
- Man:<i>...eight, seven,</i>

2046
01:50:54,181 --> 01:50:56,148
<i>six, five,</i>

2047
01:50:56,250 --> 01:50:58,751
<i>four, three,</i>

2048
01:50:58,853 --> 01:51:01,353
<i>two, one,</i>

2049
01:51:01,455 --> 01:51:03,188
<i>zero.</i>

2050
01:51:05,860 --> 01:51:08,427
Johnson's voice:
<i>These are the stakes</i>

2051
01:51:08,529 --> 01:51:12,965
<i>to make a world in which</i>
<i>all of God's children can live</i>

2052
01:51:13,067 --> 01:51:16,835
<i>or to go into the dark.</i>

2053
01:51:16,937 --> 01:51:20,372
<i>We must either</i>
<i>love each other</i>

2054
01:51:20,474 --> 01:51:22,508
<i>or we must die.</i>

2055
01:51:22,610 --> 01:51:26,679
Announcer: <i>Vote for President
Johnson</i> <i>on November 3rd.</i>

2056
01:51:26,781 --> 01:51:30,182
<i>The stakes are too high</i>
<i>for you to stay home.</i>

2057
01:51:33,854 --> 01:51:35,688
I want you to run this
right away.

2058
01:51:38,092 --> 01:51:40,492
It'll be controversial.
You'll get a lot of flak.

2059
01:51:40,594 --> 01:51:42,695
Then we'll only have
to run it once,

2060
01:51:42,797 --> 01:51:45,097
then let the press
do our work for us.

2061
01:51:46,801 --> 01:51:49,334
I wanna see it again.

2062
01:51:51,539 --> 01:51:54,840
Now, Barry Goldwater says
he's not a racist.

2063
01:51:54,942 --> 01:51:57,142
But the government
can't legislate

2064
01:51:57,244 --> 01:51:58,811
what people feel
in their hearts.

2065
01:51:58,913 --> 01:52:00,879
- Woman: That's right!
- King:<i> And he's right.</i>

2066
01:52:00,981 --> 01:52:04,416
The law can't make
white folks love you.

2067
01:52:04,518 --> 01:52:08,120
But the law can prevent them
from lynching you.

2068
01:52:09,690 --> 01:52:13,559
The law can prevent them
from denying you a job

2069
01:52:13,661 --> 01:52:16,295
and your child
an education.

2070
01:52:16,397 --> 01:52:20,165
And the law can ensure that
you have the right to vote.

2071
01:52:20,267 --> 01:52:22,501
- Amen!
- Yes!

2072
01:52:22,603 --> 01:52:27,372
I'm not here today to tell you
fine people who to vote for.

2073
01:52:27,475 --> 01:52:28,941
But come election day,

2074
01:52:29,043 --> 01:52:32,478
let's be sure to send the
fine senator from Arizona

2075
01:52:32,580 --> 01:52:36,181
and his tender heart back to
the desert where he belongs.

2076
01:52:42,123 --> 01:52:44,123
Walter...

2077
01:52:44,225 --> 01:52:45,791
was arrested?

2078
01:52:45,893 --> 01:52:49,428
YMCA men's bathroom
by the DC Vice Squad.

2079
01:52:49,530 --> 01:52:54,299
<i>The other man arrested</i>
<i>was an army staff sergeant.</i>

2080
01:52:57,037 --> 01:52:59,138
No, no, no, no.

2081
01:52:59,240 --> 01:53:00,773
This must be
some kind of mistake.

2082
01:53:00,875 --> 01:53:02,307
Hoover:
<i>No, sir.</i>

2083
01:53:02,409 --> 01:53:04,042
<i>Apparently,</i>
<i>Walter was arrested</i>

2084
01:53:04,145 --> 01:53:07,312
under similar circumstances
five years ago.

2085
01:53:08,783 --> 01:53:10,415
Now, why didn't
I know that?

2086
01:53:10,518 --> 01:53:12,351
Hoover:
<i>None of us knew.</i>

2087
01:53:12,453 --> 01:53:16,355
<i>This has Goldwater's</i>
<i>fingerprints all over it.</i>

2088
01:53:18,526 --> 01:53:20,659
Goldwater will use this.

2089
01:53:20,761 --> 01:53:23,195
God damn, this close
to the election,

2090
01:53:23,297 --> 01:53:24,897
it could be
the whole ball of wax!

2091
01:53:24,999 --> 01:53:26,632
There doesn't
appear to be

2092
01:53:26,734 --> 01:53:29,234
any security
compromise at all.

2093
01:53:30,571 --> 01:53:33,272
There damn well
better not be.

2094
01:53:33,374 --> 01:53:36,041
Your people said
they vetted him.

2095
01:53:36,143 --> 01:53:38,644
I have it in writing with
your goddamn signature on it.

2096
01:53:38,746 --> 01:53:42,681
- There are some things you can't predict.
- That's your job, Edgar.

2097
01:53:42,783 --> 01:53:45,951
I will take care of this,
Mr. President.

2098
01:53:46,053 --> 01:53:49,488
And why don't that
make me feel any better?

2099
01:53:49,590 --> 01:53:52,991
<i>You get ahold of Walter's</i>
<i>Air Force Reserve records.</i>

2100
01:53:53,093 --> 01:53:55,627
<i>Goldwater was</i>
<i>his commanding officer.</i>

2101
01:53:55,729 --> 01:53:58,564
<i>With any luck, he signed off</i>
<i>on his fitness evaluations.</i>

2102
01:53:58,666 --> 01:54:02,701
<i>We get ahold of those</i> <i>and Goldwater
won't be able</i> <i>to say shit!</i>

2103
01:54:02,803 --> 01:54:04,903
<i>Walter will resign</i>
<i>immediately.</i>

2104
01:54:05,005 --> 01:54:07,372
<i>You see to it that his doctor</i>
<i>issues a statement.</i>

2105
01:54:07,474 --> 01:54:11,376
Um, he was working too hard
and just snapped.

2106
01:54:19,887 --> 01:54:23,989
I've been working
with that man for 25 years...

2107
01:54:25,459 --> 01:54:28,227
and not a clue.

2108
01:54:38,739 --> 01:54:43,175
How do you know when...

2109
01:54:45,012 --> 01:54:47,312
somebody's...?

2110
01:54:49,817 --> 01:54:52,784
Well, there's
certain signs,

2111
01:54:52,887 --> 01:54:54,753
mannerisms.

2112
01:54:54,855 --> 01:54:58,991
The way a man dresses
or combs his hair.

2113
01:55:00,194 --> 01:55:02,327
Walks kind of funny.

2114
01:55:02,429 --> 01:55:05,030
Huh, well...

2115
01:55:05,132 --> 01:55:07,499
that's news to me.

2116
01:55:10,104 --> 01:55:12,437
I'm not questioning you.

2117
